cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of coexistence of wireless service providers in unlicensed spectrum, which involves game theory and network communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also discusses the use of TV white spaces, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The analysis of the best-response dynamics involves information theory and optimization, which are covered in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper mentions the increase of wireless data traffic, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
